---
import DocsLayout from '../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import { projects } from '../data/projects';
---

<DocsLayout title="Home" description="Legal intelligence infrastructure for Brazilian law.">
  <img src="/logo-hero.png" alt="sens.legal" class="hero-logo" />
  <p class="tagline">Legal intelligence infrastructure</p>

  <div class="waitlist-cta">
    <p>Join the waitlist for early access.</p>
    <form id="waitlist-form" class="waitlist-form">
      <input type="email" name="email" placeholder="you@example.com" required />
      <button type="submit">Join waitlist</button>
    </form>
    <p id="waitlist-msg" class="waitlist-msg" style="display:none;"></p>
  </div>

  <hr />

  <h2>What we're building</h2>

  <p>
    Frontier models reason well but can't generate reliable legal
    knowledge — they hallucinate citations, miss legal relationships, and offer
    no audit trail. As AI agents take on legal work, this gap becomes
    infrastructure-critical.
  </p>

  <p>sens.legal is that infrastructure.</p>

  <p>Four projects, each handling a different dimension of legal knowledge:</p>

  <p>
    <strong>Valter</strong> — the central jurisprudence and reasoning backend.
    The main legal backend layer of the ecosystem is being consolidated there,
    with graph-led retrieval, verification, and REST/MCP surfaces for Juca and
    external agents.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Leci</strong> — legislation. A document-first grounding engine already
    running a live <code>/api/search</code>, a functional shell, and validation
    against real data.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Douto</strong> — doctrine. A local, curated pipeline that prepares
    doctrinal artifacts for Valter rather than positioning itself as an end-user
    product.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Juca</strong> — interface. The frontend hub for briefing, reading, and
    argument-building while legal backend ownership moves out of Juca and into Valter.
  </p>

  <p>
    The architecture is model-agnostic: any LLM connects through the same
    protocols. The value isn't in the model — it's in the traceability,
    auditability, and legal structure underneath.
  </p>

  <p>Built on Brazilian Civil Law. Designed to replicate across jurisdictions.</p>

  <hr />

  <h2>Projects</h2>

  <div class="project-list">
    {projects.map((project) => (
      <div class="project-item">
        <div class="project-header">
          <h3><a href={`/projects/${project.subdomain}`}>{project.name}</a></h3>
          <span class="badge badge-dev">{project.status}</span>
        </div>
        <p class="project-desc">{project.description}</p>
        <div class="project-stack">
          {project.stack.map((tech) => (
            <code>{tech}</code>
          ))}
        </div>
        <div class="project-links">
          <a href={project.docsUrl}>Docs</a>
          <a href={project.repo} target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>

  <hr />

  <h2>Architecture</h2>

  <p>
    The ecosystem connects four projects with Valter at the center of the backend.
    Juca concentrates the user experience; Leci and Douto provide legislative and
    doctrinal grounding; and LLM agents can connect through the canonical REST API
    and MCP surfaces.
  </p>

  <pre><code class="language-mermaid">graph LR
    subgraph Interfaces
        USERS[Lawyers]
        AGENTS[LLMs / agents]
    end

    subgraph "Juca"
        JUCA[Frontend hub]
    end

    subgraph "Valter"
        API[REST API]
        MCP[MCP]
        CORE[Retrieval + reasoning]
    end

    subgraph "Grounding"
        LECI[Leci]
        DOUTO[Douto]
    end

    subgraph "Data Stores"
        PG[(PostgreSQL)]
        QD[(Qdrant)]
        N4J[(Neo4j)]
        RD[(Redis)]
    end

    USERS --> JUCA --> API
    AGENTS --> MCP --> API
    LECI --> API
    DOUTO --> API
    API --> CORE
    CORE --> PG & QD & N4J & RD</code></pre>

  <p>
    <a href="/architecture">View full architecture diagrams &rarr;</a>
  </p>
</DocsLayout>

<style>
  .hero-logo {
    display: block;
    max-width: 16rem;
    height: auto;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .tagline {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  hr {
    border: none;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    margin: var(--space-2xl) 0;
  }

  .project-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .project-item {
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .project-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .project-header h3 {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .project-desc {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .project-stack {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-xs);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .project-stack code {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
  }

  .project-links {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }

  .project-links a {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }

  .project-links a:hover {
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .waitlist-cta {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .waitlist-cta > p {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .waitlist-form {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    max-width: 28rem;
  }

  .waitlist-form input {
    flex: 1;
    padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    background: var(--color-bg);
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .waitlist-form button {
    padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 4px;
    background: var(--color-text);
    color: var(--color-bg);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    cursor: pointer;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .waitlist-form button:hover {
    opacity: 0.9;
  }

  .waitlist-msg {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    margin-top: var(--space-xs);
  }
</style>

<script>
  import mermaid from 'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/mermaid@11/dist/mermaid.esm.min.mjs';
  mermaid.initialize({ startOnLoad: false, theme: 'default' });

  document.querySelectorAll('pre:has(code.language-mermaid)').forEach((pre) => {
    const code = pre.querySelector('code');
    if (!code) return;
    const div = document.createElement('div');
    div.className = 'mermaid';
    div.textContent = code.textContent;
    pre.replaceWith(div);
  });

  mermaid.run();
</script>

<script>
  const form = document.getElementById('waitlist-form');
  const msg = document.getElementById('waitlist-msg');
  form?.addEventListener('submit', async (e) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    const btn = form.querySelector('button');
    btn.disabled = true;
    btn.textContent = '...';
    try {
      const email = form.querySelector('input[name="email"]').value;
      const res = await fetch('/api/waitlist', {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
        body: JSON.stringify({ email }),
      });
      const data = await res.json();
      if (data.ok) {
        msg.textContent = 'You\'re on the list!';
        msg.style.display = 'block';
        form.style.display = 'none';
      } else {
        msg.textContent = data.error || 'Something went wrong.';
        msg.style.display = 'block';
        btn.disabled = false;
        btn.textContent = 'Join waitlist';
      }
    } catch {
      msg.textContent = 'Something went wrong.';
      msg.style.display = 'block';
      btn.disabled = false;
      btn.textContent = 'Join waitlist';
    }
  });
</script>
